<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="567" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[811,1457,1792,2027]" pageId="6" pageNumber="567">DIAGNOSIS. — Colonies encrusting or ramose. Indistinctly stellate monticules with large, irregular vesicles forming subcircular to elongate centre and radiating inter-rays of vesicles separating rows of loosely aggregated autozooecia. Lunaria on proximal sides of autozooecia nearest the centres of monticules. Autozooecia with thin, transversely laminated walls and many, closely spaced to few, remote diaphragms; isolated by box-like to blister-like vesicles. Acanthostyles few to abundant within laminated vesicle walls or roofs. Lunaria laminated, commonly with hyaline core.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
