<subSubSection box="[132,277,375,401]" pageId="7" pageNumber="568" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[131,775,375,497]" box="[132,277,375,401]" pageId="7" pageNumber="568">COMPARISON</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="568" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[131,775,375,497]" pageId="7" pageNumber="568">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Utgaard" authorityYear="1981" box="[132,274,407,433]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Constellariidae" genus="Lunaferamita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cystoporida" pageId="7" pageNumber="568" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[132,274,407,433]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="568">Lunaferamita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Dana, 1846" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1846" box="[407,666,407,433]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Constellariidae" genus="Constellaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cystoporida" pageId="7" pageNumber="568" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[407,531,407,433]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="568">Constellaria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="DANA J. D." box="[539,666,407,433]" pageId="7" pageNumber="568" pagination="1 - 740" refId="ref20038" refString="DANA J. D. 1846. - Zoophytes. United States Exploring Expedition 7: 1 - 740. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 69333" type="journal article" year="1846">Dana, 1846</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by having lunaria and monticules of indistinct stellate shape. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Utgaard" authorityYear="1981" box="[202,344,471,497]" class="Stenolaemata" family="Constellariidae" genus="Lunaferamita" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cystoporida" pageId="7" pageNumber="568" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[202,344,471,497]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="568">Lunaferamita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses vesicles in endozones.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
